    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated History",
          "",
          "Created By:",
          "Jennifer Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "When you were living, the occult was simply one of those interesting things people dabbled in at parties. Of course, perhaps you believed it more than most, you could see the spirits of the dead. You used to think you were mad, but you quickly figured out how to parlay that into a bit of a business for yourself. You were a hit on the elite party scene in glittering New York, and made quite the name for yourself in the papers. Perhaps that's how the Tremere found you. Your abilities intrigued them, and they brought you into the clan as much for you ability to see ghosts as for your ability to hob knob with the best in society. New York for Kindred at the time was firmly a Sabbat city, but the Tremere were as entrenched there as the other sect, with the powerful Five Burroughs Chantry serving as one of the main hubs of the clan. Your influence with the elite of society went pretty far to ensure that. How could anyone think to tear down that darling, occult bookstore when you and your friends loved to gather there? Your influence with the elite ensured the clan some measure of protection over the decades until such time as the Camarilla was able to assert itself in the city once again. In the years since, the Camarilla has shifted both in leadership and outlook. Your skills were useful once, particularly amongst the keepers and harpies and other social officers of the court, but as the Toreador and Ventrue have moved in, a Tremere in that position was slowly pushed to the side. What is more, your clan in the city has had to change focus as well. Still just as powerful as it ever was, the focus on the greater chantry rather than the politics of the domain has left you without support. However, word has gotten to you of the happenings in Los Angeles. There are many whispers of what is going on there with the clan, and who might be planning what, (a lot seem to center of the Archon and Pontifex, Uleg Bey), but you know there is a Tremere prince in the city and a court in a war zone where a young, ambitious Tremere with just as much style and clout as any Toreador could make a difference. Besides, you've heard there are more mediums and spiritualists than you can shake a stick at, and perhaps there would be others to connect with, others you could maybe form a coterie with. There are many possibilities here for you in a new city, and youa re eager to find out what they are."
        ],
